DOCUMENT();       

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl"
           );
       
TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.


$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$x1 = random(2,6,2);
$y1 = random(1,5,2);
$n = random(2,5,1);
$c = random(2,18,2);
$m = -1/$n;
$disp_m = "\frac{1}{$n}";
$b = $y1 - $m*$x1;
$top_b = $y1*$n+$x1;
$bottom_b = $n;
$disp_b = "\frac{$top_b}{$bottom_b}";

$ans = "-x/$n + $top_b/$bottom_b";


BEGIN_TEXT
Question 24:
$BR $SPACE $BR
Find an equation for the line passing through the point ($x1, $y1) and perpendicular to the line \( y = $n x - $c \).  
$BR $SPACE $BR
\( y = \ \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}
END_TEXT

ANS(fun_cmp($ans,vars=>'x'));

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR
$BBOLD SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR
Since the line is perpendicular to the line \( y = $n x - $c \) $SPACE (which has slope $n), we know \( m = - \frac{1}{$n}  \)
$BR $SPACE $BR
Solving for $BITALIC b $EITALIC we have $SPACE \( f( $x1 ) = b + \left( - $disp_m \right) ($x1) \) $SPACE and therefore
$BR $SPACE $BR
\[ b = f( $x1 ) - \left( - \frac{$x1}{$n} \right)  = $y1 + \frac{$x1}{$n} = $disp_b \]
$BR $SPACE $BR
So \( f(x) = - \frac{x}{$n} + $disp_b \)
$BR
END_SOLUTION
ENDDOCUMENT();   # This should be the last executable line in the problem.